text.section:
The offices to be voted on shall be arranged on the ballot in the following order, as applicable:
public offices for which voters of the entire State may vote, in the following order:
President of the United States, or President and Vice President of the United States;
Governor and Lieutenant Governor;
Comptroller;
Attorney General; and
United States Senator;
Representative in Congress;
members of the General Assembly of Maryland, in the following order:
Senate of Maryland; and
House of Delegates;
members of the governing body of a county, in the following order:
county executive; and
county council or county commissioner;
offices in the government of the City of Baltimore, in the following order:
Mayor;
President of the City Council;
Comptroller; and
member of the City Council;
judicial offices, in the following order:
judge of the circuit court; and
appellate judges, continuance in office, in the following order:
public offices for which the voters of a county may vote, in the following order:
county treasurer;
State's Attorney;
clerk of the circuit court;
register of wills;
judge of the orphans' court;
sheriff; and
other offices filled by partisan election;
party offices; and
offices filled by nonpartisan election.
